  <h1>Green Bean Recipe</h1>
  
   
      <h2>Ingredients</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>2.50 pounds of Green Beans</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>Up to 2 quarts of Water</li>
     
      </ul>
     
   
   <h2>
     Instructions
   </h2>
  
   <p>
     <ul>
     <li>Wash beans thoroughly and snip off ends.</li>
     <li>Cut beans into segments no longer than 2 inches.</li>
     <li>In a sauce pan, bring water to a boil. You need enough water to fully cover beans.</li>
     <li>Place beans into boiling water. </li>
     <li>Add salt to water as desired. </li>
     <li>Boil beans for approximately 5 to 7 minutes or until desired texture.</li>
     <li>Use a slotted spoon to serve.</li>
  </ul>
  </p>
     
      
